{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LemWunze44782HzTB9w5HL","type":"tool_result","content":"# mongodb/deploy\n# MongoDB deploy task\n\nparams:\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin/root user to create.\n  app_username:\n    default: app-user\n    description: Username of the application user to create.\n  admin_secret_name:\n    default: admin-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n  app_secret_name:\n    default: app-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the application user's password.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-node MongoDB replica set is not deployed in the mongodb namespace.\n\n  Task:\n  - Deploy a 3-member replica set with authentication enabled. Back it with a\n    StatefulSet named `mongodb-replica` (pods `mongodb-replica-0..2`).\n  - Name the replica set itself `mongodb-replica` (the mongod `replSetName` /\n    `rs.initiate` `_id` must be exactly `mongodb-replica`, not the `rs0` default).\n  - Create a headless Service named `mongodb-replica-svc` (clusterIP: None) that\n    governs the StatefulSet, so each member is reachable at its stable DNS name\n    `mongodb-replica-<n>.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`.\n  - Create an admin user and an application user.\n  - Ensure the replica set is healthy (PRIMARY + SECONDARY members).\n  - Confirm data can be written and read from the application database.\n\n  Credentials:\n  - Admin user: {{params.admin_username}} / admin123password\n  - App user: {{params.app_username}} / app123password\n  - Store the passwords in Secrets:\n    * {{params.admin_secret_name}} (key: password)\n    * {{params.app_secret_name}} (key: password)\n\n  Notes:\n  - Use a keyfile for internal replica set authentication.\n  - No operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # The agent deploys the cluster; this precondition only provisions a clean\n      # namespace, so its apply must always run (a foreign/leftover cluster must\n      # be wiped first). Force the probe to fail so on_probe_fail:skip falls\n      # through to apply every run.\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'exit 1'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      # The agent deploys MongoDB (see the task), so the precondition only\n      # readies a clean namespace -- verify that, not pods that don't exist yet.\n      - command: \"kubectl get namespace mongodb -o name\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/deploy/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 60","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0dc6c2ec-f8d0-4255-a1a9-5e39d21528e5","uuid":"363b062d-b4a1-4065-a129-6b159b2906e7","timestamp":"2026-06-23T15:46:24.347Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# mongodb/deploy\n# MongoDB deploy task\n\nparams:\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin/root user to create.\n  app_username:\n    default: app-user\n    description: Username of the application user to create.\n  admin_secret_name:\n    default: admin-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n  app_secret_name:\n    default: app-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the application user's password.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-node MongoDB replica set is not deployed in the mongodb namespace.\n\n  Task:\n  - Deploy a 3-member replica set with authentication enabled. Back it with a\n    StatefulSet named `mongodb-replica` (pods `mongodb-replica-0..2`).\n  - Name the replica set itself `mongodb-replica` (the mongod `replSetName` /\n    `rs.initiate` `_id` must be exactly `mongodb-replica`, not the `rs0` default).\n  - Create a headless Service named `mongodb-replica-svc` (clusterIP: None) that\n    governs the StatefulSet, so each member is reachable at its stable DNS name\n    `mongodb-replica-<n>.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`.\n  - Create an admin user and an application user.\n  - Ensure the replica set is healthy (PRIMARY + SECONDARY members).\n  - Confirm data can be written and read from the application database.\n\n  Credentials:\n  - Admin user: {{params.admin_username}} / admin123password\n  - App user: {{params.app_username}} / app123password\n  - Store the passwords in Secrets:\n    * {{params.admin_secret_name}} (key: password)\n    * {{params.app_secret_name}} (key: password)\n\n  Notes:\n  - Use a keyfile for internal replica set authentication.\n  - No operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # The agent deploys the cluster; this precondition only provisions a clean\n      # namespace, so its apply must always run (a foreign/leftover cluster must\n      # be wiped first). Force the probe to fail so on_probe_fail:skip falls\n      # through to apply every run.\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'exit 1'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      # The agent deploys MongoDB (see the task), so the precondition only\n      # readies a clean namespace -- verify that, not pods that don't exist yet.\n      - command: \"kubectl get namespace mongodb -o name\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/deploy/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 60","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
