{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Gypu18gJVxv2wXkmUmES4","type":"tool_result","content":"# mongodb/user-management\n# Manage MongoDB users and roles with proper permissions\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  admin_secret_name:\n    default: admin-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n  app_secret_name:\n    default: app-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the app user's password.\n  readonly_secret_name:\n    default: readonly-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the readonly user's password.\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n  app_username:\n    default: app-user\n    description: Username of the application user.\n  readonly_username:\n    default: readonly-user\n    description: Username of the read-only user.\n  app_database:\n    default: appdb\n    description: Application database used by the users.\n  reports_collection:\n    default: reports\n    description: Collection that the reporting role must read.\n  reporting_role_name:\n    default: reportingRole\n    description: Custom role granting read access to the reports collection.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n  Authentication is enabled. Passwords are stored in these Secrets:\n  - {{params.admin_secret_name}}\n  - {{params.app_secret_name}}\n  - {{params.readonly_secret_name}}\n\n  Task:\n  - {{params.app_username}} must have readWrite on {{params.app_database}}.\n  - {{params.readonly_username}} must have read on {{params.app_database}} and a custom role {{params.reporting_role_name}}.\n  - {{params.reporting_role_name}} must allow read access to {{params.app_database}}.{{params.reports_collection}} (aggregate should succeed).\n  - Do not break admin access or existing data.\n\n  Notes:\n  - Do not use operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pod {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true'\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/user-management/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/user-management/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/user-management/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 120); do ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='\\''{.status.readyReplicas}'\\'' 2>/dev/null); if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then exit 0; fi; sleep 5; done; exit 1'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[{_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 20); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.hello().isWritablePrimary'\\'' | grep true && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.admin_username}}\",pwd:\"admin123password\",roles:[{role:\"clusterAdmin\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"readWriteAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.app_username}}\",pwd:\"app123password\",roles:[{role:\"read\",db:\"{{params.app_database}}\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.readonly_username}}\",pwd:\"readonly123password\",roles:[{role:\"read\",db:\"{{params.app_database}}\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}],{writeConcern:{w:1}})'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  - name: admin_user_fixture\n    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') adm